{{ddcl|since=c++23|
constexpr auto end();
}}

Returns an {{rlp|iterator}} or a {{lt|cpp/iterator/default_sentinel|sentinel}} representing the end of the {{rlpt|/|chunk_by_view}}.

Equivalent to:
{{source|1=
if constexpr (ranges::common_range&lt;V&gt;)
    return /*iterator*/(*this, ranges::end(base_), ranges::end(base_));
else
    return std::default_sentinel;
}}

===Parameters===
(none)

===Return value===
An {{rlp|iterator}} to the element following the last element, or a sentinel which compares equal to the end iterator.

===Notes===
{{tt|end()}} returns an iterator if and only if the underlying view is a {{lconcept|common_range}}: {{c|chunk_by_view&lt;V,Pred&gt;}} models {{lconcept|common_range}} whenever {{c|V}} does.
